review_blob: Draught at brewery. Nice pilsner with the continuous mixing of hop and sweet malt. Light, pale yellow body, silky Co2. Good work for a very high price. :(

Draught at the brewery. Nice pale-red colour, light Co2, and small bubbling foam describe the beer. Taste is nut, caramel and sweet malt with a feeling amount hop. Good work for a very high price (so overall is a little low for price).
Cheap, light yellow colour, sweet malt andf cheap, very yeastly taste for a high price. Not good at all. :(

500ml bottle. This was a fine kellerbier. It has hazy yellow colour, medium foam, medium body. Taste is good for body, medium sweet (malty) and there is a characteristic bitter from hop. Maybe there is some raisin behind these. Medium co2. Good lager!
500 ml bottle. Nice weizen, with no special taste notes, without faults and virtues. The usual citrus and sweet malt dominate, hazy yellow colour, long lasting, big foam etc etc.
Draught at Omerta, Krakow. A very nothing special lager from Poland. If youve drank lager, you can imagine this. No big fault, no virtue, no body, no crazy foam.

Draught at Omerta, Krakow. Amber colour, with good co2, creamy foam (maybe from draught). Body is normal, good to drink, not dry, and too thick. Maybe the ginger aroma what i feel is a curious. Nice for the price.
Draught at Omerta, Krakow. Nice amber colour, normal foam-co2. Taste is special, decent pine with bread and malt, some citrus. Not a very big hit, but good to drink.

500ml bottle. I bought it last week and it wasnt very fresh. It has bronze colour, nice foam, but sweet and artificial taste. Paper, sugar, some exotic fruit. You can drink, not expensive and it is not the bottom of Hungarian beers.
500ml plastic bottle. Worst plum taste beer ive ever tasted. Artificial plum (glue?), bitter and cheap citric yeast, thats all. Almost undrinkable.
500ml can. Normal beige foam, palate also medium. Taste is coffee and caramel in a halfway. It is a decent beer, not like most of Faxe beers.

500ml can. Its grain in nose and nice little bubbling foam at first sight. But foam is quickly disappearing, taste is almost poor (watery, citric with some malt). Aroma is light, there is some beer-like thing... You can drink, but not good.

500ml bottle. I have maybe opposite opinion than commercial deScription. Yeast in smell and golden color, foam is buttery, small bubbling. Taste is green: spinach, nettle. Light Co2 and medium taste is very good for this beer. Light earthy, citric hop at the end. Fine.

500ml can. It has a lot of butter-coloured foam. The beer is deep yellow, maybe golden-coloured. Medium bodied what is a little thin for the alcohol content, sometime you can feel it. Taste is typical vienna: quite sweet (toffee, malt) and clear hop at the end of all gulps.
500ml bottle. No hop in smell, and almost no hop in taste. Hard bodied lager with a lot of caramel and some fruit, hint of smoke. It is good but too much for me, i like the foam, and it hasnt.

beer_brewer_name: Bernard Family Brewery / Rodinn pivovar Bernard
review_blob: 500ml bottle. If youve ever tasted glue in elementary school, you will like this beer. :) For me this is quite medicinal, and there are the disturbing glue from hop and i dont know where. Body and other is very OK.
500ml draught. It is a citrus-bomb. There is no outstandind other taste just exotic tropical aroma (citrus). Foam is weak, body also.
500ml draught. Thick foam, orange colour, unfiltered. Sweet in smell and flowery sweetness in taste, there are also some pine and citrus. Nice, balanced, good to drink.
500ml bottle. Nice foam woth bronze body, the beer has sweet caramel odor and caramel taste with some sweetness, but there is a little grapeseed aroma too. Sticky, and not my favourite type.

beer_brewer_name: Bernard Family Brewery / Rodinn pivovar Bernard
review_blob: 500ml bottle. Nice half-dark beer with a lot of caramel and nut taste. Body is medium with good, small bubbling, long lasting foam on top. Sweetness first and bitter at the end describe. Rather dry, not sweet, well balanced. Expensive.

beer_brewer_name: Bernard Family Brewery / Rodinn pivovar Bernard
review_blob: 500ml bottle. Nothing special, a good drinking lager, what is hard for a gluten-free beer. A little floral hop, medium body, dark yellow colour, nice foam as a pillow on the liquid.

500ml can. Quite nice pilsner with hint of smoke and lot of hop, so it is characteric bitter but not too much. It has dark yellow colour, but foam is low, palate is almost watery. It is a pity, taste and aromas are very good for me.
beer_name: Urpiner Vapn Svetl 10% Classic (Draught Pale Beer)

review_blob: 500ml can. It is a normal lager, not a pils (for me). Almost sweet character with a hint of hop and yeast. Pale yellow, normal foam. Nothing special for less than 0.5 euro.

30 cl draught glass. Quite simple fruit beer with natural fruit juice, and hard alcoholic content what you cant feel, just when stand up from the chair. :) Taste is clear blueberry, so sweet and a little menthol beside the pale lager malt and hop. It is not too sweet and not too watery, not too artificial. I liked it. And cheap.

beer_brewer_name: Bernard Family Brewery / Rodinn pivovar Bernard
review_blob: 33cl bottle. It is a bad version of better ales. Czech hops - grassy, sweetness, and a lot of alcoholic warming. Nothing special, fruity, malty or so aromas. And very expensive.

30cl draught glass. Not bad fruit beer, with original sourcherry juice (from the producer). I think there is some artificial aroma also, but very little to conserve the quality. Taste is not sweet, quite clear, good. Hazy, red grapefruit coloured. Nice foam, maybe from the longer fermentation. It is a very good toy for drunkenness!

30 cl draught. It is very average hungarian home brewed lager beer. There are the cheap yeast, medium malt body, tough smoke, and a bit hop in taste. Very small foam, low Co2. Not bad, not good at least cheap.
33cl bottle. Light foam and copper colour describe it. Smell is citric and fruity, taste is citric, hoppy bitter, ment, pine and maybe a little smoke. Good, complicate beer.
33cl bottle. It has very nice aromas: sweet malt and just a little bread with surprising bitter. Body is light, almost watery, Co2 is fizzy, foam is big and quickly disapearing. Good to drink.

33cl bottle. This is a sticky, thick reddish-brown doppelbock with much of alcohol warming. Taste isnt alcoholic, rather malty with some black currant and other black fruits. Light hop at the end. Good beer, but i dont like doppelbocks. :)

300ml draught. Nice IPA with a lot of tropical fruit, orange zest and after the middle of the gulp there the herbal, medicinal hop what very good for the tropcal aromas. It has orange colour and long lasting white foam. Absolute non alcoholic, and almost not sweet. I liked it!

300ml draught. It is one of the poorest hungarian craft pilsner ive drunk. Yes, it has noble elements, but the overall... Very pale yellow colour, light Co2, small foam, only a little watery, it could good for drink. Taste is bitter, yeast, yeast, cereal, yeast and a lot of bread. Like liquid bread (indeed) with hop, but it is not good.
300ml draught. Watery, very average half-brown beer. Just simple flow the pale and the brown Holba. One of poorest czech polotmavy.
300ml draught. Simple sweetness describes this beer. Long lasting foam, nice Co2. It has very light fruity and caramellic character.
300ml draught. Another overrated czech pilsner. Bitter start - bitter end, pale yellow colour, low white foam. Some malt beside bitter. Not bad, not good.

300ml draught. It is much better than the poor light ale. There is caramel and some drak fruiteness in smell, and so on the taste. Aroma is a little citric, malty sweetness, very light smoke, and no alcoholic warming. And no foam.

300ml drauht. It is a joke. It has nice, tropical smell, opalistique yellow colour. BUT the taste and aromas: rotten egg, meat, after these some malty sweetness, and cheapest hoppy bitter at the end. Very poor beer for a huge price. I hope they will do better work for the next brew.

300ml draught. Dark brown, maybe mahagony coloured. Foam is draught. It has light Co2, but high alcohol. :) Candied fruits in the smell, but rather caramel in the taste. Almost no hop beside the alcohol and malty sweetness. Caramel is also in the taste. Nice work.

beer_brewer_name: Cski Sr Manufaktra / S.C. Lixid Project S.R.L.
review_blob: 400ml draught. Much better than normal Cski. Malty sweetness, hoppy bitterness, opal, light yellow colour. It is not a big hit, but good for drink. I think it is money-wasting for bottled normal beer. If i would be the brewery, i would bottle only this type.

beer_brewer_name: Cski Sr Manufaktra / S.C. Lixid Project S.R.L.
review_blob: 400ml draught. Foam is draught, so i dont know, white. :) Middle yellow colour, almost strong Co2. Taste is very average, rather pils type than premium lager. One-sided, hoppy bitter and long finish from this. Nothing special.

500ml bottle. Very nice dark-chocolate smell, and very dark brown colour describe it. Big, long lasting foam. Taste is quite simple, dark-choco and a little malty sweetness, some hoppy bitterness at the end. Almost watery for the intensive smell and for strong choco taste.

500ml bottle. Almost no foam (very small bubbling), and deep dark yellow colour describe the beer. Taste is sweetness what turn to caramel, and some herbal bitterness. It should be good, but i didnt like it. Short finish, a little watery.

500ml can. One most crystal clear good lager i have drank ever. It has sweet malt, light hoppy bitter at the end of all gulp and light body, but not watery. Very good and not pricy. I think much more undrikable brutal beers get more higher points...
500ml bottle. Simple like a rural redneck. It is very bready, dark yellow beer with huge foam. Clear, simple, (maybe corny?). Not the mainstream.

500ml bottle. There is sweetness and very light smoke in smell. Its taste is also these, beside sweetness there are bread and yeast, some hoppy bitter change each other. Medium body, medium yellow colour, medium foam but silk Co2.
300ml draught. The light version of big Krusovice. Light malt, very light hop, light Co2 (almost no foam). Boring, weak, watery.
500ml draught in Zdiar. It is a not too watery light pilsner with almost caramellic sweettness, grassy hoppiness, soft Co2 but long lasting small foam. Very nice for cheap price.
500ml plastic bottle. Very average beer, rather a light, sweet brown than a unique red. Sweet and ... and thats all. No foam, no body, no joy. :)

500ml can. An usual radler from Pcs. Hazy pink colour, small foam, fizzy Co2 describe the beer. Taste is better than average lemon, almost good, just too sweet and artificial. I think fewer would better (from sweetness and aroma).

500ml bottle. There is citrus in smell, and citrus in taste. It has white, medium foam for an APA and hazy, light yellow colour. Citrus and pine in mouth and a lot of hop (despite of 32 IBU, maybe for low malt content). Not will be my favourite summer drinking beer for too much hop.
